Txt_Talk_WestPort_Out_MAIN_0_ACTOR_0120_.Text: *: Wert thou the source of that ghastly commotion just now? Tell me, from whence didst thou come?
*: Oh dear. Thou appearest most fatigued. Pray enter my humble abode and tell me of what hath befallen thee.

Txt_Talk_WestPort_House_MAIN_0_ACTOR_012.Text: *: ...Thou wouldst topple the Lord of the Underworld!?
*: Clearly, thou art not one to be trifled with.
*: Nary a single soul in Alefgard would dare dream of accomplishing a feat so grand. Nay, instead we spend our days in fear of the fiend...
*: Make eastwards for the castle town of Tantegel.
*: From there, cross the seas to the south to reach the great fiend's isle.
*: That is where you will find the dread Lord of the Underworld's citadel.
*: Perchance wouldst thou have use for a map of the realm? Better it serve thee than continue to go to waste in my possession.
*: Oh, and thou art more than welcome to take the ship outside for thine own. May it aid thee on thy quest.
*: And always remember: the Goddess goeth with the brave.
*: Nary a single soul in Alefgard would dare dream of accomplishing a feat so grand. Nay, instead we spend our days in fear of the fiend...
*: Regardless, be sure to remember: the Goddess goeth with the brave.

Txt_Talk_WestPort_House_SUB_0_ACTOR_0110.Text: *: Thou hast chanced to arrive at a truly momentous juncture, stranger! Now hark thee well<--->and hold on to thy hat!
*: The Great Evil hath been put down, and peace reigneth o'er the land once more!
*: Hm? Thou knewest already of this? Th-Thou art in fact the slayer of said beast? Z-Zounds!

Txt_Talk_WestPort_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0220_0.Text: *: Travel east from here, and thou shalt come upon the mighty castle town of Tantegel erelong.
*: If thou art in need of a vessel, the boat o'er yonder belongeth to my father. Pray, avail thyself of it freely, stranger<--->'tis seldom used, if ever.

Txt_Talk_WestPort_Out_SUB_0_ACTOR_0210_0.Text: *: Huzzah! Yea, peace hath come unto our world at last!
